         <entryFree xml:id="k000280" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000280-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">qiangji</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000280-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">戧脊</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000280-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">戗脊</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000280-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">qiàngjǐ</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000280-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">ch`iang-chi</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000280-6" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000280-1" type="literal_translation">angle ridge (lit.)</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000280-7" xml:lang="en" type="literal_translation">bracing ridge (lit.)</term>
            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000280</idno>
            <note type="Note">
               <p>under construction</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">Literally “bracing ridge,” qiangji 戧脊 refers to the diagonal corner ridge of a building with a hip-gable (<term ref="/keyword/k000143">xieshan 歇山</term>) roof (Liu 1993,166）. The term qiangji 戧脊 
                  was first documented in the <term ref="/keyword/k000070">Qing</term> dynasty () and is interchangeable with “branching ridge” (<term ref="/keyword/k000281">chaji 岔脊</term>). Some modern scholars use the term qiangji to refer to the corner ridge or 
                  hipped roof (<term ref="/keyword/k000125">wudian 廡殿</term>)（Guo 2015,112）, or the corner ridge of lower roofs in a multi-story building, both of which were were called “corner ridge” (<term ref="/keyword/k000279">jiaoji 角脊</term>) in historical 
                  resources.（Qi 1999,270）</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">“戧脊”指中國古代歇山建築屋面轉角之脊(刘 1993,166）。 “戧脊”一詞最早出現於清代文獻，與岔脊同意。這一含義被現代學者沿用。此外，部分現代學者也用“戧脊”指廡殿屋面的轉角之脊（郭 2015,112），
                  或重簷建築下層簷的簷角屋脊（齐 1999,270）。但這兩種屋脊在古代文獻中均稱為角脊。</p>           
            </note>
